<!--
Resume-Clone-Template.html

WHAT THIS FILE IS
- Single-file HTML/CSS template that reproduces a simple resume landing page similar to
  https://maheshhprajapati.github.io/Resume/
- Replace the placeholder YOUR_RESUME_LINK_HERE with your resume file URL (PDF or any web link).

OPTIONS TO PUBLISH
A) Fork the original repo (if desired):
   1. Visit the original repo (if available) and fork it to your account.
   2. Replace the resume link in index.html and push to your fork.
   3. Enable GitHub Pages in repository settings (branch: main or gh-pages) -> site will be at https://<your-username>.github.io/<repo-name>/

B) Create a new repository and upload this file as index.html, then enable GitHub Pages (same steps).

QUICK HOSTING (local):
- Open this file in your browser to preview locally.
- To test on localhost quickly: `npx http-server` or `python -m http.server` in the file folder.

HOW TO REPLACE THE RESUME LINK
- Find the string YOUR_RESUME_LINK_HERE and replace it with your resume URL, e.g.:
  https://example.com/YourName-Resume.pdf
- If you want the resume to auto-download, add the `download` attribute on the anchor tag.

--- START OF HTML ---
